1:
Yahweh, I will sing forever about the ways you faithfully love me;
\q2 people not yet born will hear that you faithfully do all that you have promised.
\q1

9:
You rule over the powerful seas;
\q2 when their waves rise up, you calm them.
\q1

11:
The heavens are yours, and the earth is yours;
\q2 everything on the earth is yours because you created it all.
\q1

14:
You rule over people fairly and justly;
\q2 you are always faithfully loving us and doing what you promised.
\q1

17:
You give us your glorious strength;
\q2 because you act in our favor, we defeat our enemies.
\q1

21:
My strength will always be with him;
\q2 with my power, I will make him strong.
\q1

27:
I will give him the rights as my firstborn son;
\q2 he will be the greatest king on the earth.
\q1

34:
I will not break the agreement that I made with him;
\q2 I will not change even one word that I spoke to him.
\q1

35:
Once I made a solemn promise to David, and that will never change;
\q2 because I am God, I will never lie to David.
\q1

36:
I promised that the line of kings descended from him will go on forever;
\q2 it will last as long as the sun shines.
\q1

39:
It seems that you have broken the agreement that you made with your servant, David;
\q2 it seems as though you have thrown his crown into the dust.
\q1

41:
All those who pass by plunder his possessions;
\q2 his neighbors laugh at him.
\q1

42:
You have enabled his enemies to defeat him;
\q2 you have made them all happy.
\q1

47:
Do not forget that life is very short;
\q2 Do not forget that you have created all of us to die uselessly.
\q1
